page.title: 10Clubs in March
page.content: There are quite a lot of{clubs}in our area of March. Some of us go to{Brownies,}either to the 4th or 5th March packs. They{play {games and earn badges.}Sometimes they go on{outings}and{pack holidays. There are also the 1st March and 5th March{Girl Guides.}They do the same things as Brownies and they go on {camp. There are{Cubs}and{Scouts}in March, but they meet at the new Scout Hall which is not in our area. There is a club for{senior citizens which meets at the{GER (Great Eastern {Railway)}club each week.The{Shepherd's {Friendly Society}meets once a month at the GER,and the{Rail fans Society meets there once a month .There is also a{roller skating}club most weeks, and an{indoor bowls}club.
